## Notes Section (End of Chapter 1 / Chapter 2 Notes)

### Chapter 1 Notes (continued)

- **attention is totally focused elsewhere**: Nilli Lavie, "Attention, Distraction
  and Cognitive Control Under Load," *Current Directions in Psychological
  Science* 19 (2010): 143–48.

- **conflict between the two systems**: The classic **Stroop task** — shown a
  display of colored patches or words printed in various colors; task is to
  name the ink color while ignoring the word. Extremely difficult when colored
  words are themselves color names (e.g., GREEN printed in red).

