### Ch. 31: Risk Policies — References
- *inferior option BC*: calculation note — each combination has a sure thing and a gamble; adding the sure thing to both options of the gamble yields AD and BC
- *"locking in"*: **Thomas Langer** and **Martin Weber** — "Myopic Prospect Theory vs. Myopic Loss Aversion: How General Is the Phenomenon?" *Journal of Economic Behavior & Organization* 56 (2005): 25–38

### Ch. 32: Keeping Score — References
- *drive into a blizzard* (**sunk cost** field experiment): students who bought season theater tickets at a **reduced price** attended less than full-price buyers — especially in the first half of the season
  - Missing a show you paid full price for = closing an account in the red (loss aversion)
  - Source: **Arkes and Blumer**, "The Psychology of Sunk Costs"

