### Notes

- These pages contain no substantive argument content —
  they are the index tail, copyright page, footnotes
  (brief: "Feature introduced in detail in part 4"),
  and the title page
- The two reprinted papers are foundational:
  the 1974 *Science* paper introduced **availability**,
  **representativeness**, and **anchoring** heuristics to
  the world; the 1984 *American Psychologist* paper
  introduced **prospect theory** framing to a broad
  psychological audience

